HiRAM simulates a realistic mean monsoon circulation, precipitation, and LPS frequency compared with most CMIP5 models (
 
  SI Appendix, Figs. S1–S4
 ). The SAI (
 17), a combined measure of the frequency, intensity, and duration of LPS, shows a strong and well-defined pattern over the monsoon trough region in the HIST ensemble (
 Fig. 1
  A
 ). The horizontal structure of the SAI in HiRAM compares well with observations (Sikka archive, 1979–2003 period; ref. 
 18), albeit with an overestimation of the amplitude of the SAI distribution associated with the distribution of storm intensity’s being biased toward stronger systems (
 
  SI Appendix, Fig. S4
 ). The number of LPS simulated by HiRAM matches observations better than any other CMIP5 model.
